Green Team Twente
on Friday

📢 Competition alert!!!

We are so excited to announce a surprise for you! As our name states, we, the GREEN Team Twente, are aiming to promote sustainability and to increase the awareness about how important the environment is not only for our health, but also for our happiness!
We have been thinking hard for the last few weeks about how to express our gratitude for your support on this adventure and we thought that it is time to get to know you better!

...

We invite you to participate in #GoGreener competition and show your creativity and eco-friendly lifestyle by taking a picture with a green transportation! The most creative photo will be the winner of a GTT mug, a symbol of our appreciation and gratitude!

To enter the competition, the next steps are required:

1. Like our Facebook page

2. Tag a friend below in the comments

3. Send your creative picture in a private message on Facebook

4. (Optional): Share this post to your stories for bonus entries (we`ll be checking)

Good luck! The competition ends on Thursday, the 24th of September, at 23:59, so get in quick! Winner will be announced on Friday, the 25th of September at 15:00.

Stay tuned and don`t forget to #GoGreener! #ShellEcoMarathon #sustainability #univeristyoftwente #competition

Green Team Twente
about a month ago

On the 28th and 29th of July, three hydrogen endurance racing teams were invited by Royal NLR and DNW to test their cars in the German-Dutch Wind Tunnels. This competition was created to see which vehicle is the most aerodynamic. This gave us, together with HAN Hydromotive and Eco-Runner Team Delft an opportunity to still compete against each other despite the cancelled Shell Eco-Marathon.
We would like to thank Koninklijke NLR and DNW German-Dutch Wind Tunnels for this incre...dible experience. We learned a lot and we can use this lesson for further improvements in the future.
- - -
Video by @solidfocus

Green Team Twente
about 2 months ago

Even during the summer holidays we are not sitting around. This week we had our testing day at the university track with our 'Aurora 3'. Meanwhile we are also getting ready for another important test on the 28th and 29th of July. We will use the wind tunnel from DNW German-Dutch Wind Tunnels and our partner Koninklijke NLR to test the aerodynamic design of our vehicle. The aerodynamic capabilities are important for setting great record times at the racing track. Together with ecorunnerdelft and hanhydromotive we will show the results in an after movie somewhere in the upcoming weeks on our social media - so stay tuned.
- - -
#greenteamtwente #gogreener #aurora3 #hydrogencar #hydrogen #aerodynamics #windtunnel
